channel.title: My 3d Model
channel.description:
i started maya in may, i did alot of modelling and i was really lazy to post anything up, currently i am working on this model (trying to get some models for short animation) here it is, its not done, if you want prove i can provide i documented majority of the process, it all started from a box. for the hair i tried using nhair but got problems with it cause i did a poly mirror, so went back to tradination hair.
Any comments? yea the eye balls are not there, initally i did make them, then i had to adjust the eyes (strech) to fit her jaw complextion. her body is not done, just have the basics, leg, arm, torso,fingers, toes, etc...nothing in details yet. (the ears are supose to look like that :p all the characters would have these types of ears and big eyes).
[URL=http://img13.imagevenue.com/img.php?image=52860_Ceya_122_464lo.jpg][IMG]http://img13.imagevenue.com/loc464/th_52860_Ceya_122_464lo.jpg[/img][/URL]

item.title: My 3d Model
item.dc:creator: @SETO SETO
item.description:
@SETO wrote:

[quote=“ranger squad, post:3, topic:311817”]I call bulllshit… that’s not yours.[/quote] If you belive that i did not make it please give me proof otherwise stay where you are, i can provide about 42 screenshots as proof that i took along the making…

Sanga… initally i did wanted to be catoon like, i perfer cartoon like characters than realistic, thus i made cartoon like, but i really didn’t have any style…i never seen a increadible flim, so no idea lol. it just came to be. i didn’t have any refrence image so it all came from the head. had alot of trouble with the proportion.

currently working on her skirt and top. trying to implement nhair, but have a bit of problem with it (any maya experts here?)
